# Vercel / OpenRouter API Rules

## Secret Handling

- Never expose provider API keys to Flutter.
- Keep LLM provider keys in Vercel environment variables.
- Supabase service role keys must only be used server-side.

## API Shape

- Keep AI endpoints small and purpose-specific.
- Existing endpoints:
  - `/api/categorize` for category suggestion.
  - `/api/insight` for monthly spending insight.
  - `/api/me` for identity / entitlement.
  - `/api/dev-activate-pro` for workshop/debug activation only.

## AI Output

- Prefer structured JSON for classification.
- Normalize categories against the fixed app category list.
- Return safe fallback values when the provider response is malformed.
- Use Hong Kong Traditional Chinese in user-facing prompts and messages.

## Pro / Demo

- Real AI calls should respect entitlement or quota rules when enabled.
- Workshop demo mode should avoid blocking Tier A learners.
- Do not make Tier A depend on a working Vercel deployment.

## Error Handling

- Return clear JSON errors from API routes.
- Do not leak secrets, stack traces, provider raw errors, or service role details to clients.

